Bravo Company’s charging handles are, in my opinion, infinitely better than a standard handle.  If you would like a standard charging handle instead, I can replace it for you.  I will also include a MagPul Generation 3 30-round PMAG with the rifle.

title: For Sale:  1943 91/30 w/ BENT BOLT Mosin Nagant
postcontent:
This is a Beautiful 91/30 Mosin Nagant Rifle produced at the Soviet State Arsenal, Izhevesk in 1943. This is a grand example of a an mid war Soviet rifle. She is chambered in 7.62x54R, a very powerful and accurate round. The Metal is smooth and clean, bluing looks around 99%+. She boasts of Strong Rifling with no pitting, some light frost, there could be lots of shine left but she needs a real good cleaning. Some debris in the lands, and again everything should clean up fine. After a thorough cleaning she should make an excellent target or hunting rifle. The hardwood stock and handguard are in excellent condition, actually they look Brand New! It is smooth and clean, there are no cracks, gouges, or any other defects, only a few handling marks from storage.

This is NOT a SNIPER! She was produced with only the bent bolt, NO holes, this one was never made into a sniper. She is very rare, only a handful of the 91/30s were produced with a bent bolt. It is smooth, and actually chambers and opens much easier than a normal bolt. The secret is there is much more leverage on the bolt because of the extra size of the bolt handle.
